title: "Handshake" question miffs Edsall after loss
text:
"Handshake" question miffs Edsall after loss Embattled Maryland HC Randy Edsall sounded off during his press conference following Saturday's loss to Ohio State. COLUMBUS, Ohio (WUSA9) -- After a 49-28 loss to the number one ranked Ohio State Buckeyes on Saturday afternoon, embattled Terps head coach Randy Edsall sounded off during his press conference after being asked a question about his pregame handshakes with his players. You'll want to see @RandyEdsall 's response to a reporter asking about shaking players' hands before today's game. http://t.co/fxBT5513wT â€” BIG 10.10 (@BigTenNetwork) October 10, 2015 
Edsall entered the game under a firestorm of criticism, with reports indicating that his time in College Park could be coming to an end as early as the beginning of next week. In four-plus seasons with the Terps, Edsall's teams have yet to beat a ranked opponent.
